<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER - ENGINE GEAR TRAIN
        TIMING - INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the front cover as follows: Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e105_188.xml" xrefid="ef1050833">8.33</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply assembly grease to the three O-Rings and install into the front cover.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install a new gasket (3 segments) into the front cover. Two of the gasket segments are
                    molded pieces and the third is a bulk piece. Once the gasket segments are in place, apply RTV to the
                    joints.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the front cover on the locating dowel pins and install the mounting hardware.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten the front cover mounting bolts to the special torque value. See
                    <emph type="bold">Specifications</emph>.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
